migsp: *The MIGPUMA codes for Gwinnett County, Georgia and Dane County, Wisconsin have changed.
For 2012 and 2013 ACS, the MIGPUMAs for Gwinnett County and Richmond County, Georgia were assigned duplicate codes
of 04000.  Starting with the 2014 ACS, Gwinnett County has a MIGPUMA code of 04007.
In addition, the MIGPUMAs for northwestern Wisconsin (Ashland, Bayfield, Burnett, Douglas, Iron, Price, Rusk, Sawyer, Taylor,
and Washburn Counties) and Dane County were assigned duplicate codes of 00100.   Starting with the 2014 ACS, Dane County
The serial number (SERIALNO) and person number (SPORDER) for those records in the 2012 and 2013 PUMS files where the
MIGPUMA is Gwinnett County or Dane County can be found at the bottom of the 2012 and 2013 MIGPUMA code lists.

Roanoke, and Salem cities) in Virginia were assigned duplicate codes of 51000.  Starting with the 2015 ACS, the Charlottesville
area has a MIGPUMA code of 51001.
